abstract: Kang Min-Soo (Hangul: 강민수; born 14 February 1986) is a South Korean football player who plays at center back for Ulsan Hyundai in the K-League. He also played for Chunnam Dragons, Jeju United, Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors and Suwon BluewingsHe was a member of South Korea Olympic football team. And he is a member of South Korea national football team.His first match is 2008 Summer Olympics football qualification second round against Yemen U-23 football team at 28 February 2007. And his international debut match is Friendly match against Netherlands at 2 June 2007.
